quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  60,7,"ňĻIn time,ňļ Allah may bring about goodwill between you and those of them you ňĻnowňļ hold as enemies. For Allah is Most Capable. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,Allah does not forbid you from dealing kindly and fairly with those who have neither fought nor driven you out of your homes. Surely Allah loves those who are fair
  60,9,"Allah only forbids you from befriending those who have fought you for ňĻyourňļ faith, driven you out of your homes, or supported ňĻothersňļ in doing so. And whoever takes them as friends, then it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O believers! When the believing women come to you as emigrants,¬†test their intentions‚ÄĒtheir faith¬†is best known to Allah‚ÄĒand if you find them to be believers, then do not send them back to the disbelievers. These ňĻwomenňļ are not lawful ňĻwivesňļ for the disbelievers, nor are the disbelievers lawful ňĻhusbandsňļ for them. ňĻButňļ repay the disbelievers whatever ňĻdowriesňļ they had paid. And there is no blame on you if you marry these ňĻwomenňļ as long as you pay them their dowries. And do not hold on to marriage with polytheistic women.¬†ňĻButňļ demand ňĻrepayment ofňļ whatever ňĻdowriesňļ you had paid, and let the disbelievers do the same. That is the judgment of Allah‚ÄĒHe judges between you. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"And if any of your wives desert you to the disbelievers, and later you take spoils from them, then pay those whose wives have gone, the equivalent of whatever ňĻdowryňļ they had paid. And be mindful of Allah, in Whom you believe"
  60,12,"O Prophet! When the believing women come to you, pledging to you that they will neither associate anything with Allah ňĻin worshipňļ, nor steal, nor fornicate, nor kill their children, nor falsely attribute ňĻillegitimateňļ children to their husbands,¬†nor disobey you in what is right, then accept their pledge, and ask Allah to forgive them. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,13,"O believers! Do not ally yourselves with a people Allah is displeased with. They already have no hope for the Hereafter, just like the disbelievers lying in ňĻtheirňļ graves"
  61,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies Allah. For He ňĻaloneňļ is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  61,2,O believers! Why do you say what you do not do
  61,3,How despicable it is in the sight of Allah that you say what you do not do
  61,4,Surely Allah loves those who fight in His cause in ňĻsolidňļ ranks as if they were one concrete structure
  61,5,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when Moses said to his people, ‚ÄúO my people! Why do you hurt me when you already know I am Allah‚Äôs messenger to you?‚ÄĚ So when they ňĻpersistentlyňļ deviated, Allah caused their hearts to deviate. For Allah does not guide the rebellious people"
  61,6,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Jesus, son of Mary, said, ‚ÄúO children of Israel! I am truly Allah‚Äôs messenger to you, confirming the Torah which came before me, and giving good news of a messenger after me whose name will be AŠł•mad.‚ÄĚ¬†Yet when the Prophet came to them with clear proofs, they said, ‚ÄúThis is pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  61,7,Who does more wrong than the one who fabricates lies about Allah when invited to submit ňĻto Himňļ?¬†For Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people
  61,8,"They wish to extinguish Allah‚Äôs light with their mouths, but Allah will ňĻcertainlyňļ perfect His light, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  61,9,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ňĻtrueňļ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others, even to the dismay of the polytheists"
  61,10,O believers! Shall I guide you to an exchange that will save you from a painful punishment
  61,11,"ňĻIt is toňļ have faith in Allah and His Messenger, and strive in the cause of Allah with your wealth and your lives. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  61,12,"He will forgive your sins, and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow, and ňĻhouse you inňļ splendid homes in the Gardens of Eternity. That is the ultimate triumph"
  61,13,"ňĻHe will also give youňļ another favour that you long for: help from Allah and an imminent victory. ňĻSoňļ give good news ňĻO Prophetňļ to the believers"
  61,14,"O believers! Stand up for Allah, as Jesus, son of Mary, asked the disciples, ‚ÄúWho will stand up with me for Allah?‚ÄĚ The disciples replied, ‚ÄúWe will stand up for Allah.‚ÄĚ Then a group from the Children of Israel believed while another disbelieved. We then supported the believers against their enemies, so they prevailed"